usage: git zou [<options>]

Update zou tools, prune tags and configure all registered bundles.

    -h|--help               display help
    -v|--version            display version information
    -c|--no-config          skip bundle configuration
    -u|--no-prune-tags      do not prune tags in registered bundles
    --debug                 for development only
    --dev                   use development version (default to last stable version)

example:
    git zou -v              # display version information
    git zou                 # install the last stable version of zou tools
    git zou --dev           # install the development version of zou tools
